---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy">
	<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold dark:text-white mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
	<p class="my-4 text-md text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 mb-16">
		Last updated: April 17, 2025
	</p>

	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		At <strong class="dark:text-white">alextrs.dev</strong> we take your privacy seriously.
		This Privacy Policy describes how we handle information on the website <strong
			class="dark:text-white">alextrs.dev</strong
		>
		and in the mobile and web applications developed by Alex TRS (hereinafter, "our
		products"). By using our products, you agree to the practices described in this
		policy.
	</p>

	<!-- 1. Data Controller -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		1. Data Controller
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		The responsible party for the website and products developed under the <strong
			class="dark:text-white">alextrs.dev</strong
		>
		brand is Alex TRS, an independent software developer specialized in mobile applications
		(Android and iOS) and web applications. For any inquiries related to this policy,
		you can reach us through the contact form available at the top of the page.
	</p>

	<!-- 2. Information We Collect -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		2. Information We Collect
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Our products respect and protect your privacy. As a general rule, <strong
			class="dark:text-white"
			>we do not collect personally identifiable information</strong
		> from our users, such as names, email addresses, phone numbers, or physical addresses,
		unless you voluntarily provide it to us (for example, when contacting us directly).
	</p>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		In some cases, we may collect <strong class="dark:text-white"
			>anonymous and aggregated data</strong
		> to analyze the performance and usage of our products. This may include:
	</p>
	<ul
		class="list-disc list-inside my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 pl-4"
	>
		<li>Device type and operating system.</li>
		<li>Application or browser version in use.</li>
		<li>
			General usage data (screens visited, features used, session duration).
		</li>
		<li>Anonymous crash and error reports.</li>
		<li>Country or region of access (without precise location).</li>
	</ul>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		This data is completely anonymous and <strong class="dark:text-white"
			>cannot be linked to a specific user</strong
		>. It is used solely for statistical purposes and continuous improvement.
	</p>

	<!-- 3. Use of Data -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		3. How We Use Collected Data
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Collected data is used exclusively for the following purposes:
	</p>
	<ul
		class="list-disc list-inside my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 pl-4"
	>
		<li>
			Improving the performance, stability, and user experience of our products.
		</li>
		<li>
			Understanding how our products are used to guide future improvements.
		</li>
		<li>Detecting and fixing technical errors.</li>
		<li>Ensuring the security and proper functioning of our services.</li>
	</ul>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		<strong class="dark:text-white">We will not share, sell, or disclose</strong
		> any data to third parties for commercial or advertising purposes. We would only
		share information if required to do so by an explicit legal obligation.
	</p>

	<!-- 4. Mobile App Permissions -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		4. Mobile Application Permissions
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Some of our mobile applications for Android and iOS may request device
		permissions necessary for their proper functioning (such as access to the
		camera, storage, notifications, etc.). Each permission is requested only
		when strictly necessary for a specific feature of the app, and <strong
			class="dark:text-white"
			>your device data is never accessed without your knowledge or consent</strong
		>.
	</p>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		You can review and revoke granted permissions at any time from your device
		settings. Revoking a permission may affect the functionality of certain app
		features.
	</p>

	<!-- 5. Third-Party Services -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		5. Third-Party Services and SDKs
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Some of our products may integrate third-party tools or SDKs for features
		such as usage analytics, error reporting, or advertising. These tools may
		collect data according to their own privacy policies. Common third-party
		services we may use include:
	</p>
	<ul
		class="list-disc list-inside my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 pl-4"
	>
		<li>
			<strong class="dark:text-white"
				>Google Analytics / Firebase Analytics</strong
			> – anonymous usage analytics.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong class="dark:text-white">Google Play Services</strong> – required in
			Android apps.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong class="dark:text-white">Apple App Store Services</strong> – required
			in iOS apps.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong class="dark:text-white">Sentry / Crashlytics</strong> – anonymous crash
			and error reporting.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of these services to understand
		how they handle data. We have no control over the privacy practices of third
		parties.
	</p>

	<!-- 6. Cookies -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		6. Cookies and Similar Technologies
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Our website <strong class="dark:text-white">alextrs.dev</strong> may use essential
		technical cookies for the proper functioning of the page. These cookies do not
		store personal information and are not used for tracking or advertising purposes.
		We do not use third-party cookies for commercial purposes or behavioral tracking.
	</p>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		You can configure your browser to reject all cookies or to alert you when a
		cookie is sent. However, if you reject cookies, some parts of the site may
		not function properly.
	</p>

	<!-- 7. Security -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		7. Data Security
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect
		data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
		However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage
		is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
	</p>

	<!-- 8. Minors -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">8. Minors</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Our products are not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not
		knowingly collect personal information from children under that age. If you
		are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with
		personal information, please contact us so we can take the necessary steps.
	</p>

	<!-- 9. Your Rights -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">9. Your Rights</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Depending on the legislation applicable in your country or region, you may
		have the right to:
	</p>
	<ul
		class="list-disc list-inside my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 pl-4"
	>
		<li>Access the personal data we may hold about you.</li>
		<li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
		<li>Request deletion of your personal data.</li>
		<li>Object to or restrict the processing of your data.</li>
		<li>Request portability of your data.</li>
	</ul>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		To exercise any of these rights, you can contact us through the contact form
		available at <strong class="dark:text-white">alextrs.dev</strong>.
	</p>

	<!-- 10. Third-Party Links -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		10. Links to Third-Party Websites
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		Our products may contain links to third-party websites, repositories, or
		services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of
		those sites. We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of any external
		site before providing personal information.
	</p>

	<!-- 11. Changes -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">
		11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
	</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our
		products, practices, or legal requirements. When we do, we will update the
		"Last updated" date at the top of this page. We recommend reviewing this
		policy regularly. Continued use of our products after changes are published
		constitutes your acceptance of those changes.
	</p>

	<!-- 12. Contact -->
	<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-white mb-4 my-12">12. Contact</h2>
	<p class="my-4 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
		If you have any questions, doubts, or concerns about this Privacy Policy or
		the handling of your data, please do not hesitate to contact us through the
		contact link located at the top of the page at <strong
			class="dark:text-white">alextrs.dev</strong
		>.
	</p>
</BaseLayout>
